The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 13: Global mining major Rio Tinto and state-run NMDC Ltd are set to enter into an agreement to explore global and domestic iron ore reserves, a top official of the Indian company said. We will be entering into an MoU with Rio Tinto on August 18 for scouting mining resources in different parts of the world including in India, NMDC chairman Rana Som said.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 13: Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) has entered into a 50-50 partnership with the US-based real estate investment trust Vornado to collectively invest $500 million in a shopping mall joint venture.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 13: The Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) has issued four new standards to help companies streamline internal audits to minimise pilferage, ensure cost efficiency and mitigate waste.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 13: Purvankara Group has forayed into the affordable housing sector with the launch of its 100 per cent subsidiary, Provident Housing and Infrastructure Ltd. Priced between Rs 10 lakh and Rs 20 lakh, the homes would come up on the outskirts of tier I and tier II cities.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 13: Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd, which was recently awarded 3G spectrum to initiate high-end mobile value added services, has launched mobile television services.                                                                                                                         
